rComments: Best sta prof I have ever met! Prof Sun explains concepts in a very organized and clear way and is very caring. I hope I could take more courses with Prof Sun.

Idk why her rate is so low here. In contrast to a lot of ut stats profs, she really knows the materials well, and cares about students' mental health. Her lectures and slides are heavy but very informative. Midterm was super easy

I had to take this undegrad class for my MSc. I admit I never experienced such a badly organized lecturer with really poor teaching and communication. I know it is UofT policy to make undergrad class averages low 60 through really hard exams and artificial deflation but with her and the TA - no need for all this! We'll all automatically screw up!

Not a good Prof. her slides and 3hr long lecture are so heavy and boring. the TA is very unfair in her grading. most of the students couldn't even understand what she was saying due to her heavy accent. In short, don't take this class!

awful just awful. her slides are ok if you read the whole book but her teaching is just mediocre..i do not recommend that class. if you're looking an say 400-level STA course for your program requirements, take STA437 or STA442. those are much better

Getting awards is not enough to be a good prof. What happens when you apply for a job and you have mediocre communication skills? You simply don't get the job! The same must be applied to profs. That prof (and her TA) urgently needs to improve her communication skills, that too for a heavy 3-hr non-stop lecture. DON'T RECOMMEND AT ALL!
Extremely easy course... She doesn't do anything difficult
Not the best teacher, but she compensates by giving bonus marks on assignments and term test.
no exams, easy assign for stats students, free lunch at the last lecture, HIGHLY RECOMMENDED!!!!
